  "prompt": "How can someone subscribe to Facebook topics on Quora?",
  "response": "To subscribe to a Facebook-related topic on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Sign In**: Make sure you are logged into your Quora account. If you don't have an account, you'll need to create one first.\n\n2. **Search for a Topic**: Use the search bar at the top of the Quora homepage. Enter \"Facebook\" or a related term (e.g., \"Facebook Marketing,\" \"Facebook Privacy,\" etc.).\n\n3. **Select a Topic**: From the search results, click on the topic that interests you. Topics on Quora are usually categorized, and you\u2019ll see a list of potential matches or related topics.\n\n4. **Follow the Topic**: Once you're on the topic page, look for the \"Follow\" button, which is usually near the topic title or the top of the page. Click this button to subscribe to the topic.\n\n5. **Customization (Optional)**: After following a topic, you can customize your feed preferences. You can adjust the settings to control the frequency and type of notifications you receive about the topic in your email or notifications tab.\n\nFollowing a topic will ensure that content related to that topic will appear in your Quora feed, and you'll receive notifications or emails about new activity, depending on your settings.",
